// Problem 6:
// Write a JavaScript function with a loop that will iterate from 0 to 15. 
Each iteration, the for loop will check if the current number is odd or even and display the output.

//NOTE: This does not say whether to just print out the odd numbers or just print out the even numbers.

//your code...

//Here is the combined one, which is maybe what I think is wanted:

    function oddEvenLoop() {
        for (let i = 0; i <= 15; i++) {
            if (i % 2 !== 0) {
                console.log('odd ' + i);
            }
            else (console.log('even ' + i));
        }
    }
    oddEvenLoop();



